Session Changes — Referral Form & Admin Display                                                     
                                                                                                      
  Context                                                                                             
                                                                                                        Yesterday's commit d3697d9 ("referral from update") replaced the old multi-step ReferralForm with   
  the new QuestionnaireModal. This broke admin display (old field names) and silently broke phone-only
   submissions (API crash). Today's session fixes those issues and adds a separate phone field to the
  form.

  ---
  Issue 1 — API crashed on phone-only submissions

  File: src/app/api/leads/route.ts:53

  The new form allows submitting with email OR phone, but the API ran body.email.toLowerCase().trim() 
  unconditionally — throwing when email was null.

  // Before
  email: body.email.toLowerCase().trim(),
  // After
  email: body.email ? body.email.toLowerCase().trim() : null,

  ---
  Issue 2 — source_details was a string, not an object

  File: src/components/ndis/QuestionnaireModal.tsx (handleSubmit)

  The form sent source_details: answers.who (a single string like "myself"). The admin View modal does
   Object.entries(source_details) — iterating a string yielded [["0","m"],["1","y"],…] (the "weird    
  data showing up"). Changed to a proper object containing all questionnaire answers (mirrors
  service_matcher_answers).

  source_details: {
    who, urgency, service, funding,
    plan_management, aged_care_program, frequency,
  }

  ---
  Issue 3 — Admin "View" modal didn't show new questionnaire fields

  File: src/app/admin/referrals/page.tsx

  The admin page was looking at legacy fields (source_details.referrerType,
  source_details.primaryService) that no longer exist. The new questionnaire data lives in dedicated  
  columns: service_matcher_answers, interested_services, ndis_participant, ndis_status,
  preferred_contact.

  Changes:
  - Extended the Lead interface with ndis_participant, ndis_status, ndis_number, interested_services, 
  service_matcher_answers, preferred_contact, state. Made email nullable; source_details now
  Record<string, any> | string | null.
  - Added ANSWER_LABELS map (turns codes like "yes-ndis" → "NDIS", "few-hours" → "A few hours a week",
   etc.) covering all 7 question groups + legacy form fields.
  - Added FIELD_LABELS map for both new keys (who, urgency, service…) and legacy keys (referrerType,  
  primaryService…).
  - Added labelize(key) and labelizeValue(val) helpers (handle arrays/booleans/nulls).
  - Added getWhoFor(lead) and getPrimaryService(lead) helpers — both have legacy fallbacks so old     
  referrals still render correctly.
  - Updated table rows & mobile cards: now show "Care for" badge from getWhoFor, primary service from 
  interested_services first then legacy fields. Email cell guards on null.
  - Updated View modal:
    - Core info grid: null-safe email, plus new "Preferred Contact" and "State" cells.
    - Referral Answers section: merges service_matcher_answers + source_details (object), labelized.  
    - NDIS Information block: ndis_participant, ndis_status, ndis_number.
    - Interested Services chips.
    - Filter rendering preserves message handling.
  - Search filter (filteredLeads): null-safe email/phone with ?? false.

  ---
  Issue 4 — Same null-email crash in broader leads admin page

  File: src/app/admin/leads/page.tsx:201

  Search filter would crash on phone-only leads. Made null-safe with optional chaining + ?? false.    

  ---
  Issue 5 — sendClientConfirmation would error on phone-only leads

  File: src/lib/email.ts

  Added early return when lead.email is null — phone-only leads now skip the client confirmation email
   cleanly (admin notification still fires).

  if (!lead.email) {
    console.log(`ℹ️  Skipping client confirmation: no email on lead ${lead.id} (phone-only)`);        
    return;
  }

  ---
  Issue 6 — Type definitions out of sync with schema reality

  Files: src/types/crm.ts, src/components/admin/CommunicationPanel.tsx

  Changed email: string → email: string | null on both the canonical Lead type and
  CommunicationPanel's local interface — to match the new reality that phone-only leads exist.        

  ---
  Issue 7 — Form: split combined "Email or phone" into separate fields

  File: src/components/ndis/QuestionnaireModal.tsx

  User requested an explicit phone-number field so both email AND phone can be captured.

  Changes:
  - State: replaced single reach with emailInput + phoneInput.
  - Reset cleanup updated in handleClose.
  - Validation: contactReady requires name + at least one of (email, phone) valid; if a field is      
  filled it must pass its format check (so users can't put "abc" in email and skip).
  - handleSubmit: granular error messages — empty name / both empty / invalid email / invalid phone.  
  - Submission payload sends email and phone independently (not "either-or").
  - preferred_contact: 'either' when both supplied, else 'email' or 'phone'.
  - UI: three inputs (Name, Email, Phone) with proper type/autoComplete/inputMode. Helper hint:       
  "Provide at least one — email or phone. Both are welcome."

